[ 2026-03-05 09:26:09,023 ] 99 root - INFO - Search Results:[{'score': 0.86129683, 'chunk_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464_32', 'doc_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464', 'content': "2. **Right Branch (Decoder):** The data flows through the decoder layers. After the final decoder layer, it connects to the top of the 'Decoder' block. The output of this block feeds into the 'Classifier' at the top of the diagram.\n\nAdditionally, there is a horizontal skip connection (U-shape) connecting the output of the 'Encoder' block to the output of the 'Decoder' block. This connection bypasses the intermediate layers to allow the network to learn high-level features.\n\nThe final output of the architecture is directed to a block labeled 'Hyperspectrral Reconstruction'.*\n\n*Fig. 1 Architecture of Proposed Model*", 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 32}, {'score': 0.8526004, 'chunk_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464_3', 'doc_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464', 'content': '**Keywords:** Hyperspectral Image Classification, Deep Autoencoder, Spectral-Spatial\nFeatures, Optimizer Evaluation\n\n1\n\n---', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 3}, {'score': 0.8523087, 'chunk_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464_31', 'doc_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464', 'content': "*The image displays a schematic diagram of a neural network architecture, specifically a U-Net or a similar encoder-decoder structure, labeled with the letter 'b'. The diagram illustrates the flow of data from left to right. \n\nThe flow begins on the far left with a color image input. This input feeds into a vertical 'Encoder' block, which consists of three sequential convolutional layers: '3x3 Conv 66', '3x3 Conv 128', and '3x3 Conv 256'. \n\nFrom the output of this encoder, the architecture splits into two parallel branches. \n\n1. **Left Branch (Encoder):** The data flows through the encoder layers. After the final encoder layer, it connects to the top of the 'Encoder' block. The output of this block feeds into the 'Classifier' at the top of the diagram.", 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 31}, {'score': 0.84891933, 'chunk_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464_28', 'doc_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464', 'content': '## 4 Proposed Model\n\nThe proposed architecture, HyperspectralAE, is a hybrid model that simultaneously\nlearns spectral-spatial features through an autoencoder structure and performs clas-\nsification through an integrated classifier branch. The design begins with an encoder\ncomposed of sequential convolutional layers, batch normalization, and ReLU activa-\ntions. MaxPooling layers are strategically placed to reduce spatial dimensions while\npreserving feature richness. This encoder effectively compresses the high-dimensional\nhyperspectral input into a compact latent representation that captures the most sig-\nnificant spectral-spatial information essential for both reconstruction and classification\ntasks.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 28}, {'score': 0.84597254, 'chunk_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464_2', 'doc_id': '9f8e0d9e-a6f2-4116-835b-3d1b1c8f7464', 'content': 'lighting the method’s broad applicability and robustness. The outcomes affirm\nthat autoencoder-based deep learning approaches efficiently encode intricate\nspectral-spatial characteristics, substantially advancing accuracy and reliability\nin hyperspectral image analysis.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 2}]
